results.title: Crash Out!
results.description: Robbie lures Spider-Man to prison and into Tombstone's clutches

results.title: The Search for Robbie Robertson
results.description: Spider-Man encounters hillbilly mutants in Pennsylvania while searching for Robbie and Tombstone; Thomas Fireheart announces his takeover of the Daily Bugle

results.title: Shakedown
results.description: Spider-Man walks into the middle of a double-cross between Electro and the Shocker; Robbie finishes his business with Tombstone

results.title: The Paste and the Power (or A Very Sticky Situation)
results.description: Spider-Man gains cosmic powers; the Kingpin joins the Acts of Vengeance

results.title: There Shattered Senses or A Tale of the Brothers Grimm
results.description: The Wizard sends the Brothers Grimm against the cosmic-powered Spider-Man

results.title: The Fear and the Fury or: The Metal in Men's Souls
results.description: Doctor Doom sends the T.E.S.S.-One robot against the cosmic-powered Spider-Man

results.title: Pardoned!
results.description: Robbie Robertson pardoned for felony conviction; Spider-Man and Puma prevent Hobgoblin from assassinating him, with a little unknown help from Tombstone.

results.title: The Demon and the Dead Man
results.description: Hobgoblin busts Carrion out of a prison transport; they team-up and pay Carrion's mommy a visit; Spider-Man interrupts and is taken prisoner into the sewer.

results.title: The Carrion Cure
results.description: Spider-Man battles Carrion and Hobgoblin in the sewer; both villains allegedly die.

results.title: Bugged
results.description: While Peter and reporter Joy Mercado are on an interview with the Arranger, the Beetle attacks, aiming to kill the Arranger.

results.title: Knight and Fogg
results.description: Knight and Fogg succeed in assassinating the Arranger; Kingpin revealed to be behind the contract on the Arranger; Spider-Man resolves to pursue Knight & Fogg back to London.

results.title: The Deadly Lads From Liverpool
results.description: Spider-Man heads to England to bring Knight & Fogg to justice for the murder of the Arranger; the Chameleon calls a meeting of the Maggia; Spidey takes a dive off a bridge and hits his head while battling Knight & Fogg, he wakes aboard a fishing boat with no memory of who he is.

results.title: A Misty Kind of Memory
results.description: Spider-Man's memory returns when he dons his costume and Knight & Fogg attack, both their families become involved, and Leo Knight perishes at the hands of Fogg; Knight then turns on Fogg, making it easy for Spidey to take them both out

results.title: Sleeping Dogs
results.description: The Space Phantom, masquerading as She-Hulk, attacks Spider-Man and traps him in a hole; Spidey then goes to Avengers Mansion to pick a fight; Captain America quickly proves that it could not have been She-Hulk; Jason Jerome is making harrassing phone calls asking Mary Jane out

results.title: The Outlaw Trail
results.description: Spider-Man Gathers Puma, Prowler, Rocket Racer, and Sandman to assist him on a case involving the Avengers and a trouble-making masquerading Space Phantom, who is working for a mysterious master

results.title: Whatever Happened To the Iceman?
results.description: Peter is in California to cover the breakup of the Champions but finds only Angel has stayed in the badly constructed Champion's Tower; Spidey and Angel take on one of the Champion's former foes who is using Iceman as a pawn.

results.title: The Final Calculation
results.description: A masquerading Space Phantom causes a battle between the Outlaws and the Avengers; the Phantom is captured and tells he is working for a master whose identity he does not know; the master is revealed to be Calculus of the Young Gods who orchestrated everything so that Spidey and the Avengers would defeat a swarm of cannibal insects

results.title: Ordeal
results.description: Spider-Man and Puma go to Puma's tribal lands to settle the debt between them where they undergo a sweat lodge purification ritual wherin they see visions; Puma sells the Daily Bugle back to Jonah for $1.00; Spidey and Puma agree to fight to the death

results.title: Savage Showdown
results.description: Spider-Man and Puma duke it out in the desert in a fight to the death; they decide that they shouldn't die and shake hands; Mary jane tells off Jerome for insisting they have an affair and tells him to stay away

results.title: Creatures Stirring
results.description: Christmas Issue, Peter dunks Katzenberg in the punch bowl at the Daily Bugle Christmas party.  Spidey arrives at the family gathering at Aunt May's to find Dr. Octopus peeking through the window.  They clash until Aunt May comes outside, Doc Ock leaves so as not to disturb May, the only person who was ever kind to him.

results.title: Dedication (or, "Jonah Goes to Pieces")
results.description: Dr. Octopus attacks at the grand opening of the new Daily Bugle building, destroying a giant statue of Jonah; he and Spider-Man clash, Doc Ock threatens Mary Jane's life, then threatens to destroy the new building unless Jonah gives him $20 million dollars.

results.title: Spouse Trap
results.description: Dr. Octopus is holding the new Daily Bugle building hostage for 20 million dollars; Spider-Man and the Wild Pack drive him off; Doc Ock then kidnaps Marla Jameson and tries to ransom her for the money; Spidey foils him and the Wild Pack shows up again just in time for Ock to get away.

Essential Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Vol. (Trade Paperback)

results.title: My Friend, My Foe!
results.description: Angel and Spidey try to break Iceman out of Clark's brainwashing before their chilly friend puts them both on ice permenantly.

items.name: Essential Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Vol. (2005)
Essential Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Vol. (Trade Paperback)

results.title: The Child Within, Part 3 of 6: Shame
results.description: Harry is haunted by the ghost of his father.  It looks like he may have reached his breaking point.

results.title: The Child Within, Part 4 of 6: Guilt
results.description: The Green Goblin drugs Spider-Man and Vermin goes looking for the man who abused him in his youth.

results.title: The Child Within, Part 5 of 6: Reckonings
results.description: Spider-Man and Vermin must come to grip with childhood fears that have been bottled up for too long.

results.title: The Child Within, Part 6 of 6: Into the Dawn!
results.description: Spider-Man versus Green Goblin.  Will Harry kill Peter once and for all?

results.title: The Child Within: Aftermath
results.description: Spider-Man recruits Molten Man in the search for Harry Osborn.

results.title: Another Fine Mess!
results.description: The side-splitting superhero adventure of the year, featuring the trio nobody demanded we bring back: the White Rabbit, the Frog-Man and the Walrus! [per next issue box]

results.title: Funeral Arrangements, Part One: Settling Scores
results.description: The Vulture comes to town.  Seems the old guy's dying and wants to make peace with his enemies... by killing them.  And tops on his list are Spider-Man and Auny May! [per next issue box]

results.title: Funeral Arrangements, Part Two: Desperate Measures
results.description: The Vulture intends to set things straight with Aunt May -- just like he did with Bestman! [per next issue box]

results.title: Funeral Arrangements, Part Three: Final Judgement
results.description: Spider-Man versus the Vulture.
